### Bermuda 1726-1839 early Letters

According to Robson Lowe early letters coming from England were mentioned in Act No. 14 of 1662/23, but none appear to have survived at least in private hands. 


1773
\ph[80%]{../bermuda/1001.jpg}{

RARE EARLY COVER SENT TO U.S. "BY WAY OF BARBADOS" BY PRIVATE SHIP, ETC.; 
Fine 14 Mar. 1773 EL (family letter) from "Bermuda" sent by 
private ship (Geoff's researches suggest the 'Dolphin', Capt. Dunscomb) "To Samuel 
Coates, Merchant in Philad[elphi]a" with interesting contents ref. the writer's 
convalescing in Bermuda for the winter, mentioning a previous (Jan. 1773) 
letter sent "by the way of Carolina", but most helpfully noting the route for this letter; "...this [letter] 
comes by way of Barbados". 
Possibly a unique 18th century routing from Bermuda, and one of the earliest known covers 
from Bermuda to the U.S. Plus unrelated 1819 Bermuda Bill of Lading (for a cargo to Quebec), 
a fine small coloured c.1880 map of the islands, 
and 2 PPCs. Good lot. (5 items) \pound500.}
