INTERNAL GOVERNOR's LETTER OF PERIOD WHERE NO LOCAL P.O. SERVICE WAS ALLOWED; 
Very fine 9 May 1829 EL sent privately (by Governor's servant presumably) from "Gov[ernment].
H[ouse], Mt. Langton" to "Hamilton" written (in the third person) and signed (on the address wrapper)
by the Governor of Bermuda, <strong>Sir Hilgrove Turner</strong>; the letter asks Mr. Ewing 
for entries from baptismal registers. There was no internal island mail service from its suspension in Oct. 1821 until its resumption in 1830. Rare local letter from the military hero Sir H. Turner who claimed (amongst other things) to have personally rescued the famous Rosetta Stone from 
